snippet: Secretary of State John Kerry said the United States had made “no determinations” about efforts toward Security Council resolutions on the Middle East.
abstract: Secretary of State John Kerry says that United States is trying to encourage constructive conversation between Palestinians and Israel, and has made 'no determinations' about attempts for United Nations Security Council resolutions on Middle East peace talks.

byline.contributor: Jodi Rudoren contributed reporting from Beit Jala, West Bank.

lead_paragraph: Secretary of State John Kerry said the United States had made “no determinations” about efforts toward Security Council resolutions on the Middle East.

headline.main: U.S. Tries to Calm Latest Israeli and Palestinian Strife
headline.print_headline: U.S. Tries to Calm Latest Israeli and Palestinian Strife
